If $\text{nums}[i] = 2$, next non-prime is 4. Cost = 2.
If $\text{nums}[i] = 3$, next non-prime is 4. Cost = 1.
If $\text{nums}[i] = 4$, it's already non-prime. Cost = 0.

The total cost is the sum of costs for each element.

